<p>I have a string I'm converting from <code>"\r\n"</code> to <code>"\n"</code> line ends using:</p>  <pre><code>input.gsub(/\r\n?/, "\n") </code></pre>  <p>When I run it on my Windows host, it works fine. When I run on my Linux host, in a docker container, I get this error:</p>  <pre><code>in `gsub': invalid byte sequence in US-ASCII (ArgumentError) </code></pre>  <p>I am running Ruby 2.2. </p>